            <h4>3. Cookies</h4>
            <p>The Internet pages of Saidos Workflow may use cookies. Cookies allow us to recognize our website users and make it easier for users to utilize our website. This website itself (hosted on GitHub Pages) does not use tracking cookies or analytics tools.</p>

            <h4>4. Collection of General Data and Information</h4>
            <p>The website of Saidos Workflow collects a series of general data and information when a data subject or automated system calls up the website. This may include the browser type and version, the operating system used, the referrer URL, the hostname of the accessing computer, and the time of the server request. This information is stored in server log files and is not merged with specific personal data.</p>

            <h4>5. Routine Erasure and Blocking of Personal Data</h4>
            <p>The data controller shall process and store the personal data of the data subject only for the period necessary to achieve the purpose of storage. If the storage purpose is not applicable, or if a storage period prescribed by the European legislator expires, the personal data are routinely blocked or erased in accordance with legal requirements.</p>

            <h4>6. Rights of the Data Subject</h4>
            <p>Each data subject has the following rights granted by the European legislator:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Right of confirmation and access</strong> (Art. 15 GDPR)</li>
                <li><strong>Right to rectification</strong> (Art. 16 GDPR)</li>
                <li><strong>Right to erasure – Right to be forgotten</strong> (Art. 17 GDPR)</li>
                <li><strong>Right to restriction of processing</strong> (Art. 18 GDPR)</li>
                <li><strong>Right to data portability</strong> (Art. 20 GDPR)</li>
                <li><strong>Right to object</strong> (Art. 21 GDPR)</li>
                <li><strong>Rights regarding automated decision-making</strong> (Art. 22 GDPR)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>To exercise any of these rights, contact us at: <a href="mailto:herbasaido3@gmail.com" style="color: var(--primary-color);">herbasaido3@gmail.com</a></p>

            <h4>7. Use of Affiliate Components (Affilinet / Awin)</h4>
            <p>The controller may integrate components of affiliate networks such as Awin to process commission payments. These components may set cookies to track referral activity.</p>

            <h4>8. Use of the Meta Graph API (Facebook &amp; Instagram)</h4>
            <p>Our service integrates the <strong>Meta Graph API</strong> to enable automated content posting to Facebook Pages and Instagram Business accounts. We request only the minimum necessary permissions:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>pages_manage_posts</strong> – To publish posts to Facebook Pages</li>
                <li><strong>instagram_content_publish</strong> – To publish media to Instagram</li>
                <li><strong>pages_read_engagement</strong> – To read basic post engagement data</li>
            </ul>
            <p>We do not access your personal Facebook profile, friends list, or private messages. Access tokens are stored encrypted and never shared with third parties. By connecting your Meta account, you also agree to the <a href="https://www.facebook.com/terms.php" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--primary-color);">Meta Terms of Service</a> and <a href="https://developers.facebook.com/terms/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--primary-color);">Meta Platform Terms</a>.</p>

            <h4>9. Use of the YouTube Data API v3</h4>
            <p>Our service integrates the <strong>YouTube Data API v3</strong> (provided by Google LLC) for automated video uploads and channel management. By using this feature, you also agree to the <a href="https://www.youtube.com/t/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--primary-color);">YouTube Terms of Service</a> and <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--primary-color);">Google Privacy Policy</a>. You can revoke access at any time via <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--primary-color);">Google Security Settings</a>.</p>

            <h4>10. Use of the TikTok API</h4>
            <p>Our service may integrate the <strong>TikTok API for Developers</strong> for automated video content publishing. By connecting your TikTok account, you agree to the <a href="https://www.tiktok.com/legal/terms-of-service" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--primary-color);">TikTok Terms of Service</a>.</p>

            <h4>11. Use of Other Social Media Platform APIs</h4>
            <p>Our service may additionally integrate the following platform APIs for content posting and automation:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>LinkedIn API</strong> – For posting to LinkedIn profiles and company pages. Subject to <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/legal/user-agreement" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--primary-color);">LinkedIn User Agreement</a>.</li>
                <li><strong>Pinterest API</strong> – For creating and managing pins. Subject to <a href="https://policy.pinterest.com/terms-of-service" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--primary-color);">Pinterest Terms of Service</a>.</li>
                <li><strong>X (Twitter) API</strong> – For posting and managing content. Subject to <a href="https://twitter.com/en/tos" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--primary-color);">X Terms of Service</a>.</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>12. Data We Collect via Social Media APIs</h4>
