            </ul>

            <h4>13. Data Sharing with Third Parties</h4>
            <p>We do not sell, rent, or share your personal data with any third party for commercial purposes. Data is transmitted to platform APIs solely to fulfill the content posting service. This site is hosted on GitHub Pages – see <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--primary-color);">GitHub Privacy Statement</a>.</p>

            <h4>14. Legal Basis for the Processing</h4>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Art. 6(1)(a)</strong> – Explicit consent to connect your social media accounts.</li>
                <li><strong>Art. 6(1)(b)</strong> – Necessary to perform the content posting service.</li>
                <li><strong>Art. 6(1)(c)</strong> – Required to comply with a legal obligation.</li>
                <li><strong>Art. 6(1)(f)</strong> – Legitimate interest in improving and securing our tools.</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>15. Legitimate Interests</h4>
            <p>Our legitimate interest is to provide reliable, secure, and efficient social media automation tools that help creators and businesses manage their content across platforms.</p>

